HEADWORD: Bodyguard
<hw>Bod"y*guard`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
guard or group of guards to protect or defend the person; a
lifeguard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Retinue; attendance; following.</def> <rj><au>Bp.
Porteus.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>body shop</ent>⟦br⟧
